				<td colspan="2"><span>Here's something interesting that I noticed recently... I don't know if it's always been true or what, but even casting the RoT on the same mob twice, I can get get different levels of mitigation.  This surprised me.. I had thought that mitigation was fixed when the mob spawned, but the level of mitigation appears to be determined when the spell lands, by some &quot;roll&quot;.
<br />

<br />
So, in some cases, you might want to retry RoT on a mob when you get a &quot;Your slow was slightly (or partially) successful&quot;.
<br />
</span></td>
