				<td colspan="2"><span> I am under the impression that mobs that mitigate slow are slowable to a certain amount and not a percentage. For instance I pull with RoT 55% slow (with JF3) and it lands for full amount. When I get the mob to camp the Shammy attemps to slow it and his 75% slow  is mitigated. This tells me that the mob is slowable up to a certain amount under 75% but above 55%. If it was mitigated to a percentage than my slow also would have only partially landed. 
<br />

<br />
There a some mobs in certain zones that do mitigate RoT so I figure they are slowable to an amount under 55% and I assume Shammies, Bst's, and Chanters can only slow it to the same amount, if so all our slows would be equal on these mobs. I'm not certain on that last point but it seems that way to me.</span></td>
