		</table></td><td class="PanelBodyAlternate" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Slow mitigation<a name="66993"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 15 04 1:28 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It used to be that slows will automatically be reduced to a specific amount on mitigating mobs. This was changed some time ago - several months after PoP's release - because shamans were complaining that there were several situations where having the best slow made absolutely no difference. If the mob partially mitigated to 55%, you might as well take a beastlord or bard, since they provide additional dps or utility.
<br />

<br />
The change made it so that all slows will be mitigated by a percentage. Thus, the shaman's 75% slow will always - always - be more effective than the enchanter's, or beastlord's, or bard's.
<br />

<br />
Bard slows <i>are</i> mitigated; however, having a mod &gt;2.2 (epic + IM3 is enough, at a 2.4 mod) causes strange calculations in which the mitigation message is not delivered. Likely due to the the game trying to add the mod to the slow, causing it to wrap around, even though the mod doesn't really affect the percentage of slow, or something. In any case, it used to be that you could remove your mod item and start to see the mitigation messages again. I personally haven't tried this any time recently, and I am not certain how JF3 or added levels will affect the messages
<br />

<br />
I personally have never seen a mitigation message on <i>anything</i> since getting IM3.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
