				<td colspan="2"><span>My understanding is that NOW it does what others are saying above - a percentage is taken off the slow, so the Shammy slows are always somewhat superior.  However, if a mob does mitigate slow by, say, 66% -- well the math works out to the shaman slow now being 25% slow and my slow now being 19% and that difference really isn't as critical when you look at it.  So mitigation doesn't ever make shaman completely meaningless, but it certainly diminishes the impact if the mitigation is great enough.  But that's just the kind of methods the designers use to out maneuver us.</span></td>
