				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Slow mitigation<a name="67072"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 15 04 12:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As others have said there is a bug with slow mitigation messages in that you do not see them if your mod is above a threshold. Since I juggle my epic and have no worn mods I have often seen this happening. However I have never seen a mob give <b>different</b> mitigation messages.
<br />

<br />
Incidentally the way slow mitigation is not a fixed reduction but a % based one, at least according to the testing I have seen. For example a mob with 50% mitigation would reduce a shammy slow to 35%, and RoT (non-JF) to 26%. Right there you can see why shammies are so dreadfully underpowered in OoW xp groups.
